            <section id="legal-status" class="section">
                <h2>Legal Status of Algo Trading Under SEBI</h2>
                <p>Algorithmic trading has been legal in India since 2008 when SEBI first introduced the Direct Market Access (DMA) framework. Initially limited to institutional investors, <span class="highlight">retail participation became allowed in 2016</span> when brokers began offering API access to individual traders.</p>
                
                <h3>Current Legal Framework</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>SEBI Regulated:</strong> All algorithmic trading must comply with SEBI guidelines</li>
                    <li><strong>Exchange Approved:</strong> Algorithms must be approved by NSE/BSE</li>
                    <li><strong>Broker Facilitated:</strong> Only through SEBI-registered brokers</li>
                    <li><strong>Retail Friendly:</strong> Available to individual investors with restrictions</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="warning">
                    <strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> While algo trading is legal, <strong>unregulated platforms and unauthorized bots are not permitted</strong>. Always use SEBI-approved brokers and platforms.
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="new-regulations" class="section">
                <h2>SEBI's 2025 Regulatory Framework</h2>
                <p>Effective August 1, 2025, SEBI implemented comprehensive new rules to enhance transparency and protect retail investors:</p>
                
                <h3>Key Requirements</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Algorithm Approval:</strong> Each algorithm must receive exchange approval before deployment</li>
                    <li><strong>Unique Identifiers:</strong> All algo orders must have tracking IDs for audit trails</li>
                    <li><strong>Static IP Requirement:</strong> Traders must use whitelisted static IP addresses</li>
                    <li><strong>Manual Intervention:</strong> Full automation not allowed - human confirmation required</li>
                    <li><strong>Provider Registration:</strong> Third-party algo providers must register with exchanges</li>
                    <li><strong>Performance Validation:</strong> Agencies will validate algorithm performance claims</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h3>What This Means for Retail Traders</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>✅ <strong>Safer Environment:</strong> Reduced risk of fraud and manipulation</li>
                    <li>✅ <strong>Better Oversight:</strong> Enhanced monitoring and compliance</li>
                    <li>✅ <strong>Continued Access:</strong> Retail trading still permitted through approved channels</li>
                    <li>❌ <strong>No Full Automation:</strong> Manual order placement required</li>
                    <li>❌ <strong>Limited Platforms:</strong> Only SEBI-approved platforms allowed</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            
