            <section id="how-to-start" class="section">
                <h2>How to Start Legal Algo Trading in India</h2>
                
                <h3>Step-by-Step Process</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Choose SEBI-Registered Broker:</strong> Select from approved brokers like Zerodha, Upstox, Angel One</li>
                    <li><strong>Open Trading Account:</strong> Complete KYC and account verification</li>
                    <li><strong>Select Algo Platform:</strong> Choose Streak, Algo Lab, or API-based solution</li>
                    <li><strong>Get Static IP:</strong> Arrange whitelisted static IP address</li>
                    <li><strong>Create/Test Algorithm:</strong> Develop and backtest your strategy</li>
                    <li><strong>Get Exchange Approval:</strong> Submit algorithm for broker/exchange approval</li>
                    <li><strong>Start Paper Trading:</strong> Test with virtual money first</li>
                    <li><strong>Deploy with Real Money:</strong> Start small with manual confirmation</li>
                </ol>
                
                <div class="warning">
                    <strong>🚨 Compliance Checklist:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 0.5rem; margin-left: 1rem;">
                        <li>✅ SEBI-registered broker</li>
                        <li>✅ Exchange-approved algorithm</li>
                        <li>✅ Whitelisted static IP</li>
                        <li>✅ Manual order confirmation setup</li>
                        <li>✅ Proper risk management systems</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
