            <section id="compliance-requirements" class="section">
                <h2>Compliance Requirements</h2>
                
                <h3>For Retail Traders</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Broker Partnership:</strong> Must trade through SEBI-registered broker</li>
                    <li><strong>Platform Compliance:</strong> Use only approved algo platforms</li>
                    <li><strong>Order Limits:</strong> Follow exchange-set order frequency limits</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk Management:</strong> Implement proper position sizing and stop losses</li>
                    <li><strong>Record Keeping:</strong> Maintain trading records for compliance</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Prohibited Activities</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>❌ Using unauthorized international platforms</li>
                    <li>❌ High-frequency trading without proper authorization</li>
                    <li>❌ Market manipulation through algorithms</li>
                    <li>❌ Sharing algorithms with non-family members</li>
                    <li>❌ Bypassing broker systems with direct exchange access</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            
            <section id="faq" class="section">
                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        Can I use international algo trading platforms in India?
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>No, you must use SEBI-approved Indian brokers and platforms. International platforms are not regulated by SEBI and may violate Indian trading laws.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        Do I need programming knowledge for algo trading?
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Not necessarily. Platforms like Zerodha Streak offer visual algorithm creation without coding. However, programming knowledge (Python, JavaScript) gives you more flexibility and control.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        What is the minimum capital required for algo trading?
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>There's no specific minimum, but practical algo trading requires at least ₹50,000-1,00,000 for proper position sizing and risk management. Start with paper trading to learn first.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                        Are algo trading profits taxable in India?
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, algo trading profits are taxable as business income (for frequent traders) or capital gains (for investors). Maintain detailed records and consult a CA for tax planning.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
